==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|女|也|c1=s|c2=p|t1=female, woman|ls=psc}}.

Originally a variant of {{zh-l|姐|elder sister}}. Later repurposed as a feminine third-person pronoun influenced by European languages, with the glyph being the result of replacing the {{m|zh|人|t=person}} radical in {{m|zh|他|tr=tā}} with {{m|zh|女|t=woman}}. Linguist {{w|Liu Bannong}} is credited with coining this use around the 1910s ({{zh-ref|Bi, 2013}}).

